review_blob: A nice edition to the FTB Series. The rye backbone holds up nicely to the char.
beer_name: Left Hand Fade To Black Vol. 5: Black Rye Ale

review_blob: A solid, balanced spiced ale.  This is more about the spices (dominant) then the pumpkin (secondary) flavors.  Smooth, easy drinking,  Glad to see this being brewed back in NC by people who really love making beer.
Dont waste your money on this one.  I had three people try this from a 22 oz bottle I purchased.  It was a race to see who could pour this down the sink first.

Another disaster from Roth Brewing.  Starts with a nice, cinnamon-like aroma, but it is all downhill from there.  Hard to put into words just how bad this was.  Distinctive taste of cigarette ashes to this one.  Run, dont walk away from this one!

OMG this is awful.  Pours with almost no head.  Not as dark as a dunkel should be. Metallic aftertaste/ I am a wine & beer reseller and I taste hundreds of new craft beers every month.  Everything I have had from Roth Brewing is flat out bad.  Im guessing they put Sex in the name as a lame attempt to get someone to buy it.  Avoid these guys like the plague!earthy,

Soft strawberry aromas followed by a pleasing strawberry creme flavor.  Not a lot of weight to this one, but an OK change of pace on a hot day.  A good "bridge" beer for people who dont normally drink beer.  Better than most fruit beers on the market.

This is a sweet/chocolatey stout that goes down too smooth.  Only 6.5% ABV so I am not sure why the label says "Extra Stout."  Pour almost jet black with a full, brownish head.  A great stout for those folks who like sweetness in their brew.
Probably the smoothest hefeweizen I have had.  When the temps hit 90, this is where I am heading.

This is my first experience with Kolschs and if they are all this good, I have found a worthy alternative to wheat beers as my summertime brew.  Slighty sweet aromas, but not too aggressive.  Smooth and lush on the palate.  Slightly sweet and spicy with nice complexity and balance.  Creamy, yet brief finish.
